    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-14T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-14T08:00:00-05:00" n="510"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–1454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-14T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 14, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 206. Repeated information Saigon 70,
                    Paris 263, Hanoi 2. Delegation has been operating on assumption that situation
                    in Indochina would not deteriorate radically during coming weeks and hence that
                    time [was?] available required in order that efforts to reach common allied
                    position defense Indochina and remainder southeast Asia might crystallize. Also
                    indications here Communist bloc playing for time. In light of certain telegrams
                    reaching delegation today indicating rapidly deteriorating political and
                    military situation and persistent rumors Vietnamese-Viet Minh contacts we wonder
                    if our assumption continues valid.</p>
                <p>In view above, request Washington provide best coordinated military and political
                    estimate on situation in Indochina we are likely to be facing (1) two weeks and
                    (2) one month from now.<note n="1" xml:id="d510fn1">For the reply to this
                        request, see telegram <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 225, May 20,
                            <ref target="#pg_870">p. 870</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
